Class ArrayFeatureVector<ARRAYTYPE>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openimaj.feature.ArrayFeatureVector<ARRAYTYPE>
  • Type Parameters:
    ARRAYTYPE - Primitive a type of the backing array
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, FeatureVector, Readable, ReadableASCII, ReadableBinary, ReadWriteable, Writeable, WriteableASCII, WriteableBinary

    public abstract class ArrayFeatureVector<ARRAYTYPE>
extends Object
implements FeatureVector

      • subvector

        public abstract ArrayFeatureVector<ARRAYTYPE> subvector(int beginIndex)
        Returns a new featurevector that is a subsequence of this vector. The subsequence begins with the element at the specified index and extends to the end of this vector.
        Parameters:
        beginIndex - the beginning index, inclusive.
        Returns:
        the specified subvector.
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - if beginIndex is negative or larger than the length of this ArrayFeatureVector object.

      • subvector

        public abstract ArrayFeatureVector<ARRAYTYPE> subvector(int beginIndex,
                                                        int endIndex)
        Returns a new string that is a subvector of this vector. The subvector begins at the specified beginIndex and extends to the element at index endIndex - 1. Thus the length of the subvector is endIndex-beginIndex.
        Parameters:
        beginIndex - the beginning index, inclusive.
        endIndex - the ending index, exclusive.
        Returns:
        the specified subvector.
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the beginIndex is negative, or endIndex is larger than the length of this ArrayFeatureVector object, or beginIndex is larger than endIndex.
